WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.920 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:13.392 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:13.392 --> 00:00:21.589 align:middle line:90%


00:00:21.589 --> 00:00:23.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA MEREDITH:
If you're like me,

00:00:23.130 --> 00:00:25.940 align:middle line:84%
you become incensed when
you see someone littering.

00:00:25.940 --> 00:00:28.760 align:middle line:10%
Yet, we often turn a blind
eye to where our old tires go

00:00:28.760 --> 00:00:31.670 align:middle line:10%
after a tire change, where
our water bottles end up

00:00:31.670 --> 00:00:33.230 align:middle line:10%
when we recycle, and so forth.

00:00:33.230 --> 00:00:35.270 align:middle line:90%
But Mike Reynolds does not.

00:00:35.270 --> 00:00:38.240 align:middle line:84%
He spent decades taking our
garbage and building homes

00:00:38.240 --> 00:00:40.340 align:middle line:84%
with it, both here
and in disaster zones

00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:41.300 align:middle line:90%
around the world.

00:00:41.300 --> 00:00:43.940 align:middle line:84%
This is truly an
inspiring story.

00:00:43.940 --> 00:00:46.790 align:middle line:84%
And not only inspiring,
Mike, it's a story, to me,

00:00:46.790 --> 00:00:49.460 align:middle line:84%
above everything
else, of beauty.

00:00:49.460 --> 00:00:51.470 align:middle line:84%
Even the simplest
forms you build, to me,

00:00:51.470 --> 00:00:54.470 align:middle line:84%
are more beautiful than most of
the architecture we see around

00:00:54.470 --> 00:00:55.850 align:middle line:90%
us in this world.

00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:58.040 align:middle line:84%
And not only that,
spiritual beauty as well,

00:00:58.040 --> 00:01:01.610 align:middle line:84%
and I'm hoping we can get into
that part of the discussion

00:01:01.610 --> 00:01:03.350 align:middle line:84%
before we even launch
into the trials

00:01:03.350 --> 00:01:05.760 align:middle line:84%
and tribulations
of being a creative

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:08.270 align:middle line:84%
in a non-creative world,
for the most part.

00:01:08.270 --> 00:01:11.930 align:middle line:84%
So welcome, and maybe tell us
what your original inspiration

00:01:11.930 --> 00:01:13.250 align:middle line:90%
was, because you are a poet.

00:01:13.250 --> 00:01:14.750 align:middle line:90%
You're a visionary.

00:01:14.750 --> 00:01:18.230 align:middle line:84%
You dream a lot of these
edifices into reality.

00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:19.730 align:middle line:84%
Where did all of
this come from that

00:01:19.730 --> 00:01:21.810 align:middle line:84%
sent you down the road
as an architecture

00:01:21.810 --> 00:01:25.010 align:middle line:90%
to building bubbles for housing?

00:01:25.010 --> 00:01:29.000 align:middle line:10%
>>MIKE REYNOLDS:
Well, I think, right

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:31.680 align:middle line:10%
after architectural school,
I came to Taos, New Mexico,

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:34.730 align:middle line:10%
which was a beautiful place.

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:35.970 align:middle line:90%
And I came from the Midwest.

00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:42.170 align:middle line:84%
So in Taos, New Mexico,
there was mountains and mesas

00:01:42.170 --> 00:01:45.950 align:middle line:84%
and snow and desert,
and it was just way

00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:47.180 align:middle line:90%
different than the Midwest.

00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:52.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
set me up mentally

00:01:52.880 --> 00:01:57.860 align:middle line:84%
or emotionally to
feel things, I guess.

00:01:57.860 --> 00:02:05.300 align:middle line:10%
And the things I felt became
guiding visions or whatever

00:02:05.300 --> 00:02:12.470 align:middle line:10%
to my future, and I think that's
what put me in the position

00:02:12.470 --> 00:02:14.090 align:middle line:10%
to be doing what I'm doing now.

00:02:14.090 --> 00:02:16.250 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So the space
itself allowed your mind

00:02:16.250 --> 00:02:19.445 align:middle line:84%
to expand into all of these
concepts in a new way.

00:02:19.445 --> 00:02:23.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Yeah, I think
what happens to people

00:02:23.360 --> 00:02:28.760 align:middle line:84%
is if you can empty
your mind, really

00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:33.080 align:middle line:84%
amazing existing stuff
in the universe comes in.

00:02:33.080 --> 00:02:35.070 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
all there is to it.

00:02:35.070 --> 00:02:36.020 align:middle line:90%
It's out there.

00:02:36.020 --> 00:02:39.300 align:middle line:90%
All the information is there.

00:02:39.300 --> 00:02:40.880 align:middle line:84%
You just have to
get in a situation

00:02:40.880 --> 00:02:42.840 align:middle line:84%
where you're empty
enough to receive it,

00:02:42.840 --> 00:02:44.390 align:middle line:84%
and I think that's
what happened.

00:02:44.390 --> 00:02:46.850 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Your wife, when you
see her in the documentary,

00:02:46.850 --> 00:02:50.580 align:middle line:10%
sometimes she seems like
she's a long suffering woman.

00:02:50.580 --> 00:02:52.970 align:middle line:84%
She said, oh my god,
he's gone quiet again.

00:02:52.970 --> 00:02:54.930 align:middle line:84%
That means we've got
something brewing.

00:02:54.930 --> 00:03:00.460 align:middle line:84%
And how did her life and her
ideals fit in with your ideals

00:03:00.460 --> 00:03:03.596 align:middle line:84%
throughout all these
many years of creativity?

00:03:03.596 --> 00:03:07.880 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, she,
basically, put up with it.

00:03:07.880 --> 00:03:10.100 align:middle line:90%
But she's very creative, too.

00:03:10.100 --> 00:03:15.950 align:middle line:84%
And I think she may not always
agree with the intensity

00:03:15.950 --> 00:03:19.340 align:middle line:84%
that I will go after
things, but she

00:03:19.340 --> 00:03:23.320 align:middle line:84%
agrees that the direction
is a valid direction.

00:03:23.320 --> 00:03:27.590 align:middle line:84%
And she's there in
spirit with a lot of it

00:03:27.590 --> 00:03:29.585 align:middle line:84%
and there physically
with a lot of it.

00:03:29.585 --> 00:03:31.304 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And for
those people who

00:03:31.304 --> 00:03:32.720 align:middle line:84%
want to go further
into your work,

00:03:32.720 --> 00:03:36.020 align:middle line:84%
you also wrote a book called,
"A Coming of Wizards."

00:03:36.020 --> 00:03:39.140 align:middle line:10%
>>REYNOLDS: The book,
"A Coming of Wizards,"

00:03:39.140 --> 00:03:46.520 align:middle line:10%
is a book that came to
me in terms of a vision,

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:52.870 align:middle line:10%
I guess you would say, after
I got free in New Mexico.

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:55.470 align:middle line:84%
It was just overwhelming how
free it seemed out there.

00:03:55.470 --> 00:04:00.380 align:middle line:84%
And then it made it
so I could receive

00:04:00.380 --> 00:04:04.140 align:middle line:90%
what is out there anyway.

00:04:04.140 --> 00:04:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And so that's how I ended
up writing this book,

00:04:08.210 --> 00:04:09.610 align:middle line:90%
"A Coming of Wizards."

00:04:09.610 --> 00:04:14.110 align:middle line:84%
And I actually go back
and look at it today,

00:04:14.110 --> 00:04:17.390 align:middle line:84%
and the things that
were said in there

00:04:17.390 --> 00:04:22.340 align:middle line:84%
still guide me today about
the pragmatic application

00:04:22.340 --> 00:04:23.480 align:middle line:90%
of this kind of thinking.

00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:26.600 align:middle line:90%


00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:29.570 align:middle line:90%
There was an actual incident.

00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:32.810 align:middle line:84%
I talk about it
sometimes, but I don't

00:04:32.810 --> 00:04:36.890 align:middle line:84%
like to get too
woo-woo with any of it.

00:04:36.890 --> 00:04:42.500 align:middle line:84%
I want it to be very pragmatic,
so people can accept it.

00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:47.010 align:middle line:84%
But it was a dream,
vision type thing.

00:04:47.010 --> 00:04:50.630 align:middle line:84%
And I was into pyramids and
am into pyramids, in terms of,

00:04:50.630 --> 00:04:52.760 align:middle line:84%
there is something going
on with the pyramids.

00:04:52.760 --> 00:04:54.470 align:middle line:84%
Look all over the
planet, there are

00:04:54.470 --> 00:04:56.390 align:middle line:90%
pyramids all over the planet.

00:04:56.390 --> 00:04:58.610 align:middle line:84%
So there was a
reason for building

00:04:58.610 --> 00:05:01.820 align:middle line:84%
these things, specifically
aligned and magnetically

00:05:01.820 --> 00:05:05.750 align:middle line:84%
aligned, and they involved
crystal and a lot of things.

00:05:05.750 --> 00:05:07.610 align:middle line:90%
So I experimented with them.

00:05:07.610 --> 00:05:10.010 align:middle line:84%
I had a bed in the
King's Chamber level

00:05:10.010 --> 00:05:12.260 align:middle line:84%
of a perfectly
proportioned pyramid.

00:05:12.260 --> 00:05:13.340 align:middle line:90%
I slept in it.

00:05:13.340 --> 00:05:14.720 align:middle line:90%
I spent a lot of time there.

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:15.985 align:middle line:90%
I had a dream there.

00:05:15.985 --> 00:05:20.990 align:middle line:84%
The dream was the impetus
of "A Coming of Wizards"

00:05:20.990 --> 00:05:26.840 align:middle line:84%
book that turned me
on to thinking, that

00:05:26.840 --> 00:05:30.920 align:middle line:84%
allowed me to get
away and look back

00:05:30.920 --> 00:05:33.170 align:middle line:90%
at where we are on this planet.

00:05:33.170 --> 00:05:37.730 align:middle line:84%
And it caused me to want to
take a very pragmatic approach

00:05:37.730 --> 00:05:43.010 align:middle line:84%
to trying to make that happen
in a way that wasn't just words

00:05:43.010 --> 00:05:46.960 align:middle line:90%
and magic and spiritual talk.

00:05:46.960 --> 00:05:50.750 align:middle line:84%
I took it to a very
pragmatic level,

00:05:50.750 --> 00:05:52.640 align:middle line:84%
and that's how the
earthship itself,

00:05:52.640 --> 00:05:56.000 align:middle line:84%
as a building concept, a
sustainable building concept,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:56.980 align:middle line:90%
came about.

00:05:56.980 --> 00:05:59.700 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, years
ago, many, many years ago,

00:05:59.700 --> 00:06:02.217 align:middle line:84%
I saw a movie called
"Slaughterhouse-Five."

00:06:02.217 --> 00:06:03.800 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if you
remember that one.

00:06:03.800 --> 00:06:04.883 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Vaguely, yeah.

00:06:04.883 --> 00:06:08.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Anyway, he ends up
in this alternate world of his,

00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:10.070 align:middle line:90%
living in a bubble in space.

00:06:10.070 --> 00:06:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And that became my
ideal for a home.

00:06:12.380 --> 00:06:15.620 align:middle line:84%
Living in, literally,
a Plexiglas bubble

00:06:15.620 --> 00:06:18.230 align:middle line:84%
in the middle of a redwood
forest with some light pouring

00:06:18.230 --> 00:06:20.210 align:middle line:90%
in would be my ideal structure.

00:06:20.210 --> 00:06:23.390 align:middle line:84%
But anything that I
have been in in my life,

00:06:23.390 --> 00:06:26.030 align:middle line:84%
right down to the home I
own in Sedona right now,

00:06:26.030 --> 00:06:29.360 align:middle line:84%
the notion of these
rounded spaces

00:06:29.360 --> 00:06:33.240 align:middle line:84%
creates a completely different
experience and potential.

00:06:33.240 --> 00:06:34.340 align:middle line:90%
Can you talk about that?

00:06:34.340 --> 00:06:37.815 align:middle line:84%
Because your structures
are all rounded and domed.

00:06:37.815 --> 00:06:43.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, I think
what we're looking at,

00:06:43.130 --> 00:06:46.130 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what we call
biotecture-- we don't even

00:06:46.130 --> 00:06:48.380 align:middle line:84%
call it architecture anymore,
because I don't really

00:06:48.380 --> 00:06:53.270 align:middle line:84%
agree that architecture is
addressing our current needs,

00:06:53.270 --> 00:06:55.940 align:middle line:84%
physically or emotionally
or spiritually

00:06:55.940 --> 00:06:56.970 align:middle line:90%
or in any other way.

00:06:56.970 --> 00:07:04.130 align:middle line:84%
But we're really trying to
give ourselves the opportunity

00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:08.990 align:middle line:84%
and make people have the
opportunity to feel the earth,

00:07:08.990 --> 00:07:09.790 align:middle line:90%
to be--

00:07:09.790 --> 00:07:11.870 align:middle line:84%
to recognize that they
are part of the earth.

00:07:11.870 --> 00:07:14.240 align:middle line:84%
If we recognize we're
part of the earth,

00:07:14.240 --> 00:07:18.500 align:middle line:84%
then we're not
going to destroy it.

00:07:18.500 --> 00:07:22.860 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it's
like, my hand is out here,

00:07:22.860 --> 00:07:24.680 align:middle line:90%
so maybe I'm not aware of it.

00:07:24.680 --> 00:07:28.580 align:middle line:84%
But really, if I'm
not aware of my hand,

00:07:28.580 --> 00:07:33.530 align:middle line:84%
I can have it be damaged
and not even know it.

00:07:33.530 --> 00:07:34.930 align:middle line:90%
The earth is an extension of us.

00:07:34.930 --> 00:07:36.970 align:middle line:84%
We're an extension
of the earth, really.

00:07:36.970 --> 00:07:43.390 align:middle line:84%
And if we can make the dwelling
spaces, the sustainable vessels

00:07:43.390 --> 00:07:51.530 align:middle line:84%
that people live in, keep them
aware of the entire physique

00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:55.160 align:middle line:84%
of the earth, then
we won't be trying

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:57.440 align:middle line:90%
to beg people to not destroy it.

00:07:57.440 --> 00:08:00.110 align:middle line:84%
They'll naturally treat it
like they treat their own body.

00:08:00.110 --> 00:08:03.890 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Truly, and when
it comes to architecture,

00:08:03.890 --> 00:08:06.200 align:middle line:84%
seems like, certainly,
in modern history,

00:08:06.200 --> 00:08:10.340 align:middle line:84%
relatively modern history,
the last 1,000 years or so--

00:08:10.340 --> 00:08:13.160 align:middle line:84%
granted, there have been some
beautiful Gothic constructions

00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:15.530 align:middle line:84%
and such, where
this arched energy

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:16.980 align:middle line:90%
is taken into consideration.

00:08:16.980 --> 00:08:21.380 align:middle line:84%
But by and large, people have
constructed boxes to live in.

00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:23.120 align:middle line:90%
This isn't how nature works.

00:08:23.120 --> 00:08:27.560 align:middle line:84%
There are very few examples
of boxes in nature, right?

00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:29.810 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Right.

00:08:29.810 --> 00:08:34.669 align:middle line:84%
I think the box architecture
that we are experiencing now

00:08:34.669 --> 00:08:40.280 align:middle line:84%
is a direct result
of the box thinking.

00:08:40.280 --> 00:08:44.280 align:middle line:84%
We are kind of in a box as
far as our thinking goes

00:08:44.280 --> 00:08:47.370 align:middle line:84%
and as far as our feeling
goes, and we don't really

00:08:47.370 --> 00:08:48.170 align:middle line:90%
get out of it.

00:08:48.170 --> 00:08:50.447 align:middle line:84%
So naturally, the
things we build

00:08:50.447 --> 00:08:51.530 align:middle line:90%
are going to reflect that.

00:08:51.530 --> 00:08:55.230 align:middle line:90%


00:08:55.230 --> 00:08:58.640 align:middle line:84%
I've tried to change it,
evolve it, and everything.

00:08:58.640 --> 00:09:01.940 align:middle line:84%
But now, I'm into
another phase of it,

00:09:01.940 --> 00:09:05.280 align:middle line:84%
in terms of just
trying to transcend it,

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:07.455 align:middle line:90%
because it's there in cities.

00:09:07.455 --> 00:09:09.410 align:middle line:90%
And it's all over the world.

00:09:09.410 --> 00:09:13.160 align:middle line:84%
You're not going to change
that, but you can transcend it.

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:16.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
important, because we're

00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:22.000 align:middle line:84%
on a planet that is not really
doing too well with this.

00:09:22.000 --> 00:09:26.990 align:middle line:84%
And the result is, we are
going to be left alone,

00:09:26.990 --> 00:09:28.250 align:middle line:90%
not the planet.

00:09:28.250 --> 00:09:29.480 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:09:29.480 --> 00:09:33.750 align:middle line:10%
One of the people I've admired
historically in modern times

00:09:33.750 --> 00:09:35.610 align:middle line:10%
is Rudolf Steiner,
on a lot of levels.

00:09:35.610 --> 00:09:38.990 align:middle line:10%
And one of them was his notion
of space and architecture

00:09:38.990 --> 00:09:42.090 align:middle line:10%
and the lack of use
of right angles,

00:09:42.090 --> 00:09:44.390 align:middle line:10%
if it could at all be avoided.

00:09:44.390 --> 00:09:46.610 align:middle line:84%
And I think one of
the things people

00:09:46.610 --> 00:09:48.650 align:middle line:84%
have found interesting
about his work,

00:09:48.650 --> 00:09:50.510 align:middle line:84%
like his original
Goetheanum, which

00:09:50.510 --> 00:09:53.180 align:middle line:84%
was two interlocking
domes, is that you

00:09:53.180 --> 00:09:55.160 align:middle line:90%
can't see the means of support.

00:09:55.160 --> 00:09:57.500 align:middle line:84%
Is it simply that it's
so much more difficult

00:09:57.500 --> 00:09:59.150 align:middle line:90%
to build a domed space?

00:09:59.150 --> 00:10:04.616 align:middle line:84%
Is that why we're in this
functional boxed reality?

00:10:04.616 --> 00:10:08.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, our
world, in my opinion,

00:10:08.790 --> 00:10:12.460 align:middle line:90%
is run on economics these days.

00:10:12.460 --> 00:10:15.580 align:middle line:84%
Economy, money is
almost like God,

00:10:15.580 --> 00:10:19.480 align:middle line:90%
and that controls everything.

00:10:19.480 --> 00:10:22.880 align:middle line:84%
You can't have water,
power, sewage, food,

00:10:22.880 --> 00:10:26.380 align:middle line:84%
shelter without going
through money to get to it.

00:10:26.380 --> 00:10:30.640 align:middle line:84%
And that ends up governing our
thinking and our architecture,

00:10:30.640 --> 00:10:34.600 align:middle line:84%
and so it is an
expression of that.

00:10:34.600 --> 00:10:38.530 align:middle line:84%
And I think, in nature, nature
has nothing to do with money.

00:10:38.530 --> 00:10:41.300 align:middle line:84%
Trees don't have
to buy anything.

00:10:41.300 --> 00:10:45.250 align:middle line:84%
They simply grow out of
and are part of nature.

00:10:45.250 --> 00:10:48.160 align:middle line:84%
And if we could do that,
I'm sure our architecture

00:10:48.160 --> 00:10:49.120 align:middle line:90%
would change.

00:10:49.120 --> 00:10:52.090 align:middle line:84%
Our architecture that
we call biotecture

00:10:52.090 --> 00:10:59.300 align:middle line:84%
now is organically
expressing this thinking.

00:10:59.300 --> 00:11:03.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
will be in the future

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:08.795 align:middle line:84%
if we can somehow transcend
this place that we're in now.

00:11:08.795 --> 00:11:10.420 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And you
call them earthships.

00:11:10.420 --> 00:11:11.503 align:middle line:90%
Your homes are earthships.

00:11:11.503 --> 00:11:13.591 align:middle line:84%
You've been doing this
for over 30 years, right?

00:11:13.591 --> 00:11:15.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Over
40 years, actually.

00:11:15.090 --> 00:11:16.120 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Over 40 years.

00:11:16.120 --> 00:11:20.890 align:middle line:84%
And all of these structures
are domed in nature.

00:11:20.890 --> 00:11:22.660 align:middle line:84%
When I see it, it
just lifts my heart

00:11:22.660 --> 00:11:25.270 align:middle line:84%
to see these structures,
even the simplest, most

00:11:25.270 --> 00:11:28.984 align:middle line:84%
rudimentary ones, because you
can feel your way into that

00:11:28.984 --> 00:11:30.900 align:middle line:84%
and what it would be
like to be in that space.

00:11:30.900 --> 00:11:34.440 align:middle line:90%


