00:12:20.680 --> 00:12:24.250 align:middle line:10%
to build, in terms of
longevity of the materials,

00:12:24.250 --> 00:12:27.580 align:middle line:10%
because bottles and cans and
tires are made very well.

00:12:27.580 --> 00:12:29.890 align:middle line:10%
But here's the most
important thing.

00:12:29.890 --> 00:12:34.510 align:middle line:10%
These materials are indigenous
to the entire planet.

00:12:34.510 --> 00:12:35.800 align:middle line:90%
I've been all over the world.

00:12:35.800 --> 00:12:38.430 align:middle line:84%
Every country has got
cans, tires, and bottles.

00:12:38.430 --> 00:12:41.840 align:middle line:84%
They're right at arm's
reach for us to use.

00:12:41.840 --> 00:12:44.650 align:middle line:84%
And if you came here
from another planet,

00:12:44.650 --> 00:12:46.970 align:middle line:84%
you would look at them
as, they grow here.

00:12:46.970 --> 00:12:49.090 align:middle line:84%
They're natural
products of this planet.

00:12:49.090 --> 00:12:52.690 align:middle line:84%
So I don't look at them
as garbage anymore.

00:12:52.690 --> 00:12:57.130 align:middle line:84%
I don't even use the
word garbage in my mind,

00:12:57.130 --> 00:12:59.000 align:middle line:84%
because there's no
such thing as it.

00:12:59.000 --> 00:13:01.420 align:middle line:84%
We invented the
concept of garbage,

00:13:01.420 --> 00:13:04.280 align:middle line:84%
because we don't know what to
do with a lot of our byproducts.

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:08.140 align:middle line:84%
But to me, tires, cans,
bottles are natural resources

00:13:08.140 --> 00:13:12.200 align:middle line:84%
of this planet that are
very useful in building

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:14.890 align:middle line:84%
our sustainable
vessels of the future.

00:13:14.890 --> 00:13:16.450 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's
talk about that.

00:13:16.450 --> 00:13:20.156 align:middle line:84%
