comfortable shelter

00:14:02.220 --> 00:14:04.280 align:middle line:90%
that doesn't use fossil fuels.

00:14:04.280 --> 00:14:05.860 align:middle line:90%
One of them is electricity.

00:14:05.860 --> 00:14:06.850 align:middle line:90%
One of them is water.

00:14:06.850 --> 00:14:08.350 align:middle line:90%
One of them is food.

00:14:08.350 --> 00:14:10.970 align:middle line:84%
One of them is what
to do with sewage.

00:14:10.970 --> 00:14:12.970 align:middle line:84%
And one of them is what
to do with this thing we

00:14:12.970 --> 00:14:14.110 align:middle line:90%
call garbage.

00:14:14.110 --> 00:14:19.280 align:middle line:84%
Every country, city has to
address these six things.

00:14:19.280 --> 00:14:22.990 align:middle line:84%
So in our process of making
every single building address

00:14:22.990 --> 00:14:27.070 align:middle line:84%
those six things, it ends
up being organic looking,

00:14:27.070 --> 00:14:30.550 align:middle line:84%
and it's not just
addressing economy.

00:14:30.550 --> 00:14:34.540 align:middle line:84%
It's addressing the six things
that humans need for sustenance

00:14:34.540 --> 00:14:35.340 align:middle line:90%
on this planet.

00:14:35.340 --> 00:14:38.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And the buildings, the
way you've moved them forward

00:14:38.230 --> 00:14:42.370 align:middle line:84%
