I can't blame that person.

00:34:06.140 --> 00:34:08.120 align:middle line:84%
Even though they're
trying to put me in jail,

00:34:08.120 --> 00:34:09.889 align:middle line:90%
I still can't blame that person.

00:34:09.889 --> 00:34:11.880 align:middle line:90%
They grew up thinking that way.

00:34:11.880 --> 00:34:15.780 align:middle line:84%
And so I went through
several phases of this.

00:34:15.780 --> 00:34:19.639 align:middle line:84%
It used to be I hid
from building inspectors

00:34:19.639 --> 00:34:23.030 align:middle line:84%
and avoided them and
things like that,

00:34:23.030 --> 00:34:25.250 align:middle line:84%
because I knew I
was doing things

00:34:25.250 --> 00:34:28.031 align:middle line:84%
that-- building buildings out
of what they call garbage.

00:34:28.031 --> 00:34:30.530 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, you didn't have
permits, you just had ideas.

00:34:30.530 --> 00:34:32.239 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: It got
scary that way.

00:34:32.239 --> 00:34:35.420 align:middle line:84%
So my next method
of trying to do this

00:34:35.420 --> 00:34:38.960 align:middle line:84%
was to join them, so I went to
the legislature in New Mexico.

00:34:38.960 --> 00:34:42.230 align:middle line:84%
I spent four years
lobbying and presenting

00:34:42.230 --> 00:34:44.389 align:middle line:90%
and finally got a law passed.

00:34:44.389 --> 00:34:45.620 align:middle line:90%
That was horrible.

00:34:45.620 --> 00:34:48.710 align:middle line:84%
I would never spend four years
of my life doing that again,

00:34:48.710 --> 00:34:50.970 align:middle line:84%
but it was my attempt
at joining them.

00:34:50.970 --> 00:34:51.770 align:middle line:90%
It did work.

00:34:51.770 --> 00:34:54.230 align:middle line:84%
Governor Bill Richardson
signed the bill,

00:34:54.230 --> 00:34:56.630 align:middle line:84%
and it is an Act
in New Mexico now.

00:34:56.630 --> 00:35:02.790 align:middle line:84%
But that took too long, and
that was not a viable answer.

00:35:02.790 --> 00:35:04.260 align:middle line:90%
So now, I'm looking at--

00:35:04.260 --> 00:35:07.530 align:middle line:90%


00:35:07.530 --> 00:35:10.100 align:middle line:84%
well, here's the way I
explain it to myself,

00:35:10.100 --> 00:35:13.010 align:middle line:84%
is like, if you have a
dog and it has worms,

00:35:13.010 --> 00:35:15.900 align:middle line:84%
you try to cram a worm
pill down the dog's throat.

00:35:15.900 --> 00:35:17.180 align:middle line:90%
And you get bit.

00:35:17.180 --> 00:35:18.860 align:middle line:90%
He spits it back up.

00:35:18.860 --> 00:35:20.195 align:middle line:90%
He doesn't like it.

00:35:20.195 --> 00:35:22.070 align:middle line:84%
But if you take that
worm pill and you put it

00:35:22.070 --> 00:35:25.370 align:middle line:84%
in a ball of hamburger, throw
it at the dog, he swallows it.

00:35:25.370 --> 00:35:28.490 align:middle line:84%
So that's the way
I look at it now.

00:35:28.490 --> 00:35:32.150 align:middle line:84%
I know what the
world wants and what

00:35:32.150 --> 00:35:36.110 align:middle line:84%
they're capable of
receiving, and I

00:35:36.110 --> 00:35:40.460 align:middle line:84%
take what we want to
do and put it in that.

00:35:40.460 --> 00:35:42.710 align:middle line:84%
And they don't even
notice it, and it's

00:35:42.710 --> 00:35:46.970 align:middle line:84%
causing us to be able to--
without stress, without war,

00:35:46.970 --> 00:35:49.130 align:middle line:84%
without conflict,
it's causing us

00:35:49.130 --> 00:35:52.310 align:middle line:84%
to be able to transcend
the situation that we're

00:35:52.310 --> 00:35:53.756 align:middle line:90%
in throughout the world.

00:35:53.756 --> 00:35:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But
initially, what you

00:35:55.130 --> 00:35:58.280 align:middle line:84%
were trying to do with this bill
was just have a zone set aside

00:35:58.280 --> 00:36:00.350 align:middle line:84%
where you could be
free to experiment.

00:36:00.350 --> 00:36:01.990 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: It
seemed very logical.

00:36:01.990 --> 00:36:03.156 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It seemed logical.

00:36:03.156 --> 00:36:04.680 align:middle line:90%
You had the land.

00:36:04.680 --> 00:36:07.490 align:middle line:84%
Why would government
concern itself

00:36:07.490 --> 00:36:12.950 align:middle line:84%
to the point of anger and
filibustering and so forth?

00:36:12.950 --> 00:36:14.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Yes,
they're not seeing.

00:36:14.480 --> 00:36:17.180 align:middle line:84%
We test airplanes,
and it kills people.

00:36:17.180 --> 00:36:18.260 align:middle line:90%
We test automobiles.

00:36:18.260 --> 00:36:19.550 align:middle line:90%
People get killed.

00:36:19.550 --> 00:36:20.720 align:middle line:90%
We test drugs.

00:36:20.720 --> 00:36:22.220 align:middle line:90%
Really, it's ridiculous.

00:36:22.220 --> 00:36:25.430 align:middle line:84%
And the one thing that
almost got them thinking

00:36:25.430 --> 00:36:27.200 align:middle line:90%
was here in New Mexico--

00:36:27.200 --> 00:36:31.550 align:middle line:84%
in New Mexico, we
tested the atomic bomb,

00:36:31.550 --> 00:36:33.830 align:middle line:90%
and it blew apart 10,000 acres.

00:36:33.830 --> 00:36:36.140 align:middle line:90%
So it's still polluted today.

00:36:36.140 --> 00:36:42.890 align:middle line:84%
So why can't we take 10 acres
and test methods of living?

00:36:42.890 --> 00:36:48.430 align:middle line:90%
But it hits nerves or something.

00:36:48.430 --> 00:36:49.580 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It does.

00:36:49.580 --> 00:36:52.190 align:middle line:84%
The amount of anger
that was engendered

00:36:52.190 --> 00:36:54.920 align:middle line:84%
in some of these people
is really quite shocking.

00:36:54.920 --> 00:36:58.370 align:middle line:84%
What do you feel they
felt under threat by?

00:36:58.370 --> 00:37:01.085 align:middle line:90%


00:37:01.085 --> 00:37:03.425 align:middle line:84%
Or they just don't like
people doing things outside

00:37:03.425 --> 00:37:04.225 align:middle line:90%
of the rules.

00:37:04.225 --> 00:37:05.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, that.

00:37:05.240 --> 00:37:09.794 align:middle line:84%
But the first time
I told an engineer

00:37:09.794 --> 00:37:11.960 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to build
a house out of beer cans--

00:37:11.960 --> 00:37:16.246 align:middle line:84%
he was my older mentor
that I was looking up to.

00:37:16.246 --> 00:37:18.620 align:middle line:84%
And I told him I had this
great idea to build a house out

00:37:18.620 --> 00:37:20.230 align:middle line:90%
of beer cans.

00:37:20.230 --> 00:37:21.420 align:middle line:90%
It was in a bar.

00:37:21.420 --> 00:37:22.220 align:middle line:90%
He stood up--

00:37:22.220 --> 00:37:24.219 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: That's where
those good ideas come up.

00:37:24.219 --> 00:37:25.730 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: In a bar.

00:37:25.730 --> 00:37:29.150 align:middle line:84%
And he stormed out of
the bar read in the face

00:37:29.150 --> 00:37:32.330 align:middle line:84%
saying I was a disgrace to
the architectural community

00:37:32.330 --> 00:37:34.280 align:middle line:84%
for wanting to build
out of garbage.

00:37:34.280 --> 00:37:38.330 align:middle line:84%
In other words, human
waste and garbage

00:37:38.330 --> 00:37:40.640 align:middle line:84%
are things that
people don't want

00:37:40.640 --> 00:37:45.140 align:middle line:90%
to consider as a good thing.

00:37:45.140 --> 00:37:50.360 align:middle line:84%
Biologically, they are good, and
garbage is a natural resource.

00:37:50.360 --> 00:37:54.980 align:middle line:84%
And I want the things
that nobody else wants.

00:37:54.980 --> 00:37:56.530 align:middle line:90%
It's almost like alchemy.

00:37:56.530 --> 00:38:00.110 align:middle line:84%
I can turn them into things
that we need for our life.

00:38:00.110 --> 00:38:03.260 align:middle line:84%
Human waste turns into
food if it's done right.

00:38:03.260 --> 00:38:06.290 align:middle line:84%
Garbage turns into
building materials.

00:38:06.290 --> 00:38:10.910 align:middle line:84%
One of my things on this planet
that I would consider to be

00:38:10.910 --> 00:38:13.880 align:middle line:90%
a mentor-type thing is a tree.

00:38:13.880 --> 00:38:16.070 align:middle line:84%
A tree has what we
would call garbage.

00:38:16.070 --> 00:38:18.200 align:middle line:84%
It drops its leaves
on the ground,

00:38:18.200 --> 00:38:20.750 align:middle line:84%
and they turn into
dirt for more trees.

00:38:20.750 --> 00:38:23.840 align:middle line:84%
They're not in wrappers
like our garbage.

00:38:23.840 --> 00:38:27.710 align:middle line:84%
They make more soil
for more trees.

00:38:27.710 --> 00:38:30.440 align:middle line:84%
The tree breathes
out oxygen, and it

00:38:30.440 --> 00:38:33.350 align:middle line:90%
breathes in carbon dioxide.

00:38:33.350 --> 00:38:35.930 align:middle line:84%
The tree absorbs
energy from the sun.

00:38:35.930 --> 00:38:38.360 align:middle line:84%
The tree absorbs nutrients
and water from the earth

00:38:38.360 --> 00:38:39.590 align:middle line:90%
and from the rain.

00:38:39.590 --> 00:38:43.610 align:middle line:84%
It's sitting there, encountering
the phenomena of the planet,

00:38:43.610 --> 00:38:46.155 align:middle line:84%
and we call ourselves
intelligent?

00:38:46.155 --> 00:38:47.840 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right, exactly.

00:38:47.840 --> 00:38:49.760 align:middle line:84%
So this happened, what--
was it three times?

00:38:49.760 --> 00:38:50.850 align:middle line:84%
Three attempts
before you finally--

00:38:50.850 --> 00:38:51.680 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Four.

00:38:51.680 --> 00:38:53.210 align:middle line:90%
We got it on the fourth attempt.

00:38:53.210 --> 00:38:56.870 align:middle line:84%
Each time, I got a
little more savvy

00:38:56.870 --> 00:38:59.550 align:middle line:84%
about how to handle
myself there.

00:38:59.550 --> 00:39:02.840 align:middle line:84%
And I was definitely
out of my element

00:39:02.840 --> 00:39:06.150 align:middle line:84%
and don't ever want
to do it again.

00:39:06.150 --> 00:39:17.690 align:middle line:84%
But it was impressive, to me,
to see that if you kept at it,

00:39:17.690 --> 00:39:20.870 align:middle line:90%
people will start hearing you.

00:39:20.870 --> 00:39:26.500 align:middle line:84%
And it had to do with
Governor Bill Richardson, too.

00:39:26.500 --> 00:39:30.110 align:middle line:84%
He's a thinker, and
he's a good governor.

00:39:30.110 --> 00:39:31.150 align:middle line:90%
He was a good governor.

00:39:31.150 --> 00:39:38.280 align:middle line:84%
And he saw that what we were
doing could make some sense.

00:39:38.280 --> 00:39:40.870 align:middle line:84%
He said, you're on to
something, and he ended up

00:39:40.870 --> 00:39:42.040 align:middle line:90%
signing the bill.

00:39:42.040 --> 00:39:45.910 align:middle line:84%
Whereas, there are a lot
of legislators that--

00:39:45.910 --> 00:39:47.710 align:middle line:84%
they have-- I
remember, there's one

00:39:47.710 --> 00:39:51.280 align:middle line:84%
in the movie that just says,
global warming is a myth.

00:39:51.280 --> 00:39:53.920 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's fine,
let him think that.

00:39:53.920 --> 00:39:56.200 align:middle line:84%
I don't think he
thinks that now.

00:39:56.200 --> 00:39:57.730 align:middle line:90%
Things are changing.

00:39:57.730 --> 00:39:59.290 align:middle line:90%
You can't convince people.

00:39:59.290 --> 00:40:00.820 align:middle line:90%
You have to show people.

00:40:00.820 --> 00:40:09.160 align:middle line:84%
And I don't really ever
challenge people in an agro way

00:40:09.160 --> 00:40:10.160 align:middle line:90%
or anything.

00:40:10.160 --> 00:40:14.524 align:middle line:84%
You simply have to put it
out there, here's water.

00:40:14.524 --> 00:40:15.940 align:middle line:84%
Do you want to
drink it, or do you

00:40:15.940 --> 00:40:17.981 align:middle line:84%
want to wait a while until
you're dying of thirst

00:40:17.981 --> 00:40:19.474 align:middle line:90%
and drink it?

00:40:19.474 --> 00:40:21.640 align:middle line:84%
That's a way we're trying
to put this out there now.

00:40:21.640 --> 00:40:23.620 align:middle line:84%
Not cram it down
people's throats,

00:40:23.620 --> 00:40:26.060 align:middle line:90%
just, here is what we've found.

00:40:26.060 --> 00:40:28.900 align:middle line:90%


00:40:28.900 --> 00:40:34.150 align:middle line:84%
I think one of the ways I look
at what we're doing now is--

00:40:34.150 --> 00:40:38.180 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a genius that
thought up all of this stuff.

00:40:38.180 --> 00:40:40.330 align:middle line:84%
I'm just using
biology and physics

00:40:40.330 --> 00:40:44.230 align:middle line:84%
that's already there, eighth
grade biology and physics.

00:40:44.230 --> 00:40:47.800 align:middle line:84%
The way I look at what we're
doing is I compare it to like,

00:40:47.800 --> 00:40:51.370 align:middle line:84%
you're in a subway and
the subway caved in,

00:40:51.370 --> 00:40:56.230 align:middle line:84%
and you've got 70 people there
in pitch black total darkness.

00:40:56.230 --> 00:41:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And I looked over and I saw a
teeny, teeny, little pinpoint

00:41:00.250 --> 00:41:01.390 align:middle line:90%
of light.

00:41:01.390 --> 00:41:03.800 align:middle line:84%
I went over there, and I
started pulling a few rocks away

00:41:03.800 --> 00:41:04.600 align:middle line:90%
from it.

00:41:04.600 --> 00:41:05.980 align:middle line:90%
And it got a little bigger.

00:41:05.980 --> 00:41:09.730 align:middle line:84%
And other people saw that
and came over and started

00:41:09.730 --> 00:41:11.590 align:middle line:90%
helping me pull rocks away.

00:41:11.590 --> 00:41:12.730 align:middle line:90%
That's what's going on.

00:41:12.730 --> 00:41:15.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You have to
show people a better way.

00:41:15.190 --> 00:41:19.390 align:middle line:84%
So you were able to get
the permits and such to be

00:41:19.390 --> 00:41:22.840 align:middle line:90%
able to do the subdivision.

00:41:22.840 --> 00:41:25.990 align:middle line:84%
You won, but you were building
repetitive little houses.

00:41:25.990 --> 00:41:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
things that really

00:41:27.580 --> 00:41:31.090 align:middle line:84%
got me was hearing from the
other people in the community

00:41:31.090 --> 00:41:35.350 align:middle line:84%
saying, when this
mindset came in,

00:41:35.350 --> 00:41:36.940 align:middle line:84%
they felt like they
lost their ability

00:41:36.940 --> 00:41:39.880 align:middle line:90%
to really dream any longer.

00:41:39.880 --> 00:41:42.640 align:middle line:84%
And you said, we
lost our ability

00:41:42.640 --> 00:41:45.774 align:middle line:84%
to simply make mistakes
and learn from them.

00:41:45.774 --> 00:41:46.690 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about that.

00:41:46.690 --> 00:41:52.360 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, I think, in
our world, our developed world

00:41:52.360 --> 00:41:55.450 align:middle line:90%
today, a mistake is a lawsuit.

00:41:55.450 --> 00:41:57.865 align:middle line:84%
A mistake is a take
your credentials.

00:41:57.865 --> 00:42:01.030 align:middle line:84%
A mistake is a bad
reputation and a bad review

00:42:01.030 --> 00:42:04.480 align:middle line:90%
on the internet.

00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:06.040 align:middle line:90%
Mistakes are considered bad.

00:42:06.040 --> 00:42:08.530 align:middle line:84%
Just like human waste
is considered bad,

00:42:08.530 --> 00:42:11.905 align:middle line:84%
garbage is considered bad,
mistakes are considered bad.

00:42:11.905 --> 00:42:14.800 align:middle line:84%
I look at all of those
things as positives.

00:42:14.800 --> 00:42:19.130 align:middle line:84%
We learned this thing that
we're doing from trial and error

00:42:19.130 --> 00:42:24.070 align:middle line:84%
mistakes, and I've made
millions of mistakes.

00:42:24.070 --> 00:42:26.430 align:middle line:84%
But each one, I
learned a little more.

00:42:26.430 --> 00:42:28.660 align:middle line:84%
If you do something
that's successful,

00:42:28.660 --> 00:42:30.380 align:middle line:90%
you haven't learned anything.

00:42:30.380 --> 00:42:33.190 align:middle line:84%
And so we just keep
making the mistakes

00:42:33.190 --> 00:42:35.710 align:middle line:84%
and learning more
about the earth,

00:42:35.710 --> 00:42:38.290 align:middle line:84%
about the phenomena
of the earth.

00:42:38.290 --> 00:42:41.770 align:middle line:84%
And that's an education
that's ongoing for us.

00:42:41.770 --> 00:42:47.080 align:middle line:84%
And so we on this planet,
in this day and age,

00:42:47.080 --> 00:42:49.210 align:middle line:90%
mistakes are taboo.

00:42:49.210 --> 00:42:51.310 align:middle line:84%
I think that should
be changed, too.

00:42:51.310 --> 00:42:55.780 align:middle line:84%
We should encourage mistakes and
not have the stigma around them

00:42:55.780 --> 00:42:56.815 align:middle line:90%
that we have today.

00:42:56.815 --> 00:42:58.600 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I think
there's a university--

00:42:58.600 --> 00:42:59.620 align:middle line:90%
the name is eluding me.

00:42:59.620 --> 00:43:02.620 align:middle line:84%
I think there's a
university in California,

00:43:02.620 --> 00:43:05.570 align:middle line:84%
its theme is the
university of failure,

00:43:05.570 --> 00:43:07.760 align:middle line:90%
which is how you learn.

00:43:07.760 --> 00:43:08.920 align:middle line:90%
I love that idea.

00:43:08.920 --> 00:43:11.470 align:middle line:84%
Because in life,
everyone, every parent

00:43:11.470 --> 00:43:13.360 align:middle line:84%
will say, oh, we learn
through mistakes.

00:43:13.360 --> 00:43:15.400 align:middle line:84%
But once it gets to an
institutional level,

00:43:15.400 --> 00:43:18.070 align:middle line:84%
once it becomes something
under someone else's purview,

00:43:18.070 --> 00:43:20.125 align:middle line:84%
you're not allowed to
make mistakes anymore.

00:43:20.125 --> 00:43:24.350 align:middle line:90%


00:43:24.350 --> 00:43:27.610 align:middle line:84%
Was that a bit of a heavy
hearted moment for you,

00:43:27.610 --> 00:43:30.020 align:middle line:84%
to know that everything you
were going to do now was

00:43:30.020 --> 00:43:32.500 align:middle line:84%
going to be closely
scrutinized and regulated?

00:43:32.500 --> 00:43:35.800 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Well, yes it was.

00:43:35.800 --> 00:43:38.590 align:middle line:84%
I always squirm around and
figure out a way, I guess.

00:43:38.590 --> 00:43:42.610 align:middle line:84%
But I have found myself
in recent history--

00:43:42.610 --> 00:43:46.360 align:middle line:84%
we've won some battles, and
we are able to do some things.

00:43:46.360 --> 00:43:49.100 align:middle line:90%


00:43:49.100 --> 00:43:52.270 align:middle line:84%
The world is evolving
to the extent

00:43:52.270 --> 00:43:57.094 align:middle line:84%
that one out of every 10
regulators is aware of the fact

00:43:57.094 --> 00:43:58.510 align:middle line:84%
that we need to
make some changes.

00:43:58.510 --> 00:44:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And they will go there with an
earthship idea, and they'll go,

00:44:02.350 --> 00:44:03.250 align:middle line:90%
I love those things.

00:44:03.250 --> 00:44:04.750 align:middle line:90%
I want it to happen.

00:44:04.750 --> 00:44:06.890 align:middle line:90%
We'll help you get through.

00:44:06.890 --> 00:44:09.410 align:middle line:84%
Then there's a bunch of
them that say, no way.

00:44:09.410 --> 00:44:15.640 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, on this
planet, it's getting to be more

00:44:15.640 --> 00:44:18.130 align:middle line:90%
and more people are aware of it.

00:44:18.130 --> 00:44:21.970 align:middle line:84%
But there are places on
this planet that I run to.

00:44:21.970 --> 00:44:24.970 align:middle line:84%
I went to Indonesia,
to a deserted island,

00:44:24.970 --> 00:44:27.340 align:middle line:84%
and we built there
with no rules.

00:44:27.340 --> 00:44:29.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: This is so cool.

00:44:29.230 --> 00:44:31.570 align:middle line:90%
I want to get to that.

00:44:31.570 --> 00:44:35.930 align:middle line:84%
Let's bring it up to the
year 2005 and the tsunami.

00:44:35.930 --> 00:44:39.450 align:middle line:84%
Were you the one that was
contacted by this one man

00:44:39.450 --> 00:44:41.170 align:middle line:90%
in the Andaman Islands?

00:44:41.170 --> 00:44:43.180 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Yeah.

00:44:43.180 --> 00:44:45.910 align:middle line:84%
Even then, it was
out around the world,

00:44:45.910 --> 00:44:49.030 align:middle line:84%
to some extent, what we were
doing and attempting to do.

00:44:49.030 --> 00:44:51.160 align:middle line:84%
So an architect from
the tsunami islands--

00:44:51.160 --> 00:44:54.970 align:middle line:84%
I mean, from the Andaman
Islands contacted me and said,

00:44:54.970 --> 00:44:57.510 align:middle line:84%
the time for-- it was
a very short message--

00:44:57.510 --> 00:45:00.950 align:middle line:84%
the time for dropping
meds and food is over.

00:45:00.950 --> 00:45:03.400 align:middle line:84%
It's time for something
real to happen,

00:45:03.400 --> 00:45:07.130 align:middle line:84%
to help us get out of
this and grow out of it.

00:45:07.130 --> 00:45:10.180 align:middle line:90%
And will you come and help us?

00:45:10.180 --> 00:45:14.260 align:middle line:84%
So I went to my bank-- and
I've got a good rapport

00:45:14.260 --> 00:45:18.100 align:middle line:84%
with the bank-- and I
said, I need $50,000

00:45:18.100 --> 00:45:20.297 align:middle line:90%
to go help these people.

00:45:20.297 --> 00:45:21.380 align:middle line:90%
And that was on a Tuesday.

00:45:21.380 --> 00:45:22.810 align:middle line:90%
On a Thursday, I had the money.

00:45:22.810 --> 00:45:24.160 align:middle line:90%
We got our shots, and we went.

00:45:24.160 --> 00:45:27.450 align:middle line:90%


00:45:27.450 --> 00:45:29.915 align:middle line:90%
But I learned from that.

00:45:29.915 --> 00:45:31.060 align:middle line:90%
We do that a lot now.

00:45:31.060 --> 00:45:33.680 align:middle line:84%
We're going to
Puerto Rico now, too.

00:45:33.680 --> 00:45:42.310 align:middle line:84%
But I found that a major
disaster is a hole in dogma.

00:45:42.310 --> 00:45:44.270 align:middle line:90%
They are so needy from--

00:45:44.270 --> 00:45:45.070 align:middle line:90%
they need water.

00:45:45.070 --> 00:45:45.910 align:middle line:90%
They need shelter.

00:45:45.910 --> 00:45:47.110 align:middle line:90%
They need everything.

00:45:47.110 --> 00:45:49.630 align:middle line:84%
They don't care about
any rules or regulations.

00:45:49.630 --> 00:45:51.260 align:middle line:90%
They just need water.

00:45:51.260 --> 00:45:52.510 align:middle line:10%
They need shelter.

00:45:52.510 --> 00:45:55.600 align:middle line:10%
And so when those things happen,
like that earthquake in Haiti

00:45:55.600 --> 00:45:59.050 align:middle line:10%
and so on, the people,
as well as the regulators

00:45:59.050 --> 00:46:02.670 align:middle line:10%
and the people that
run the government,

00:46:02.670 --> 00:46:05.225 align:middle line:10%
there's just a giant hole in
dogma, and we go through it.

00:46:05.225 --> 00:46:06.850 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: Yeah,
creativity can flourish

00:46:06.850 --> 00:46:07.960 align:middle line:10%
under those conditions.

00:46:07.960 --> 00:46:11.770 align:middle line:10%
So with this particular
experience, first of all 3/4

00:46:11.770 --> 00:46:14.620 align:middle line:10%
of the population was gone.

00:46:14.620 --> 00:46:16.980 align:middle line:84%
Peoples' families were
completely broken apart.

00:46:16.980 --> 00:46:20.200 align:middle line:90%
They really, truly had nothing.

00:46:20.200 --> 00:46:22.060 align:middle line:84%
At the end, seeing
this little dome

00:46:22.060 --> 00:46:25.060 align:middle line:84%
and seeing these gutters that
allowed for the rainwater

00:46:25.060 --> 00:46:28.220 align:middle line:84%
to be captured and seeing
the little, green hand-pump

00:46:28.220 --> 00:46:30.460 align:middle line:84%
inside so that they
could literally

00:46:30.460 --> 00:46:33.340 align:middle line:84%
source their own water
from inside their dwelling,

00:46:33.340 --> 00:46:37.330 align:middle line:84%
I just found so
inspiring and beautiful.

00:46:37.330 --> 00:46:41.130 align:middle line:84%
And you say, they
called it magic.

00:46:41.130 --> 00:46:44.350 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Yeah, they do.

00:46:44.350 --> 00:46:47.290 align:middle line:84%
Several times, it's been
called magic, what we do.

00:46:47.290 --> 00:46:52.030 align:middle line:84%
But really, magic is
simply understanding

00:46:52.030 --> 00:46:55.570 align:middle line:84%
the phenomena of this
planet and going with them.

00:46:55.570 --> 00:46:59.920 align:middle line:84%
And we keep getting
better at that.

00:46:59.920 --> 00:47:04.480 align:middle line:84%
And we do go to places
after disasters for one,

00:47:04.480 --> 00:47:07.870 align:middle line:84%
to help the people with what
we've learned, but also,

00:47:07.870 --> 00:47:11.500 align:middle line:84%
because we get to learn there,
and we have a place there

00:47:11.500 --> 00:47:14.780 align:middle line:84%
where we are not
regulated and controlled.

00:47:14.780 --> 00:47:20.510 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a mutual situation,
a mutual beneficiary situation.

00:47:20.510 --> 00:47:22.660 align:middle line:84%
And like I say, we
have made a practice

00:47:22.660 --> 00:47:25.980 align:middle line:84%
of going to those
places after disasters.

00:47:25.980 --> 00:47:28.580 align:middle line:90%
We're in Puerto Rico right now.

00:47:28.580 --> 00:47:32.820 align:middle line:84%
And then we also go to places
where there is no disaster,

00:47:32.820 --> 00:47:34.330 align:middle line:90%
but where there's no people.

00:47:34.330 --> 00:47:36.250 align:middle line:90%
And that's fantastic, too.

00:47:36.250 --> 00:47:40.270 align:middle line:84%
In other words, to go to
some deserted island and just

00:47:40.270 --> 00:47:42.370 align:middle line:84%
start doing what we know
how to do because we

00:47:42.370 --> 00:47:45.370 align:middle line:84%
can go to an island
where there's nothing

00:47:45.370 --> 00:47:49.690 align:middle line:84%
and end up, like in Indonesia,
with two little earthships that

00:47:49.690 --> 00:47:52.960 align:middle line:84%
have 6,000 gallons of
water, high speed internet,

00:47:52.960 --> 00:47:57.140 align:middle line:84%
electricity, the best
flushing toilet in Indonesia.

00:47:57.140 --> 00:48:01.030 align:middle line:84%
We know we can settle the
earth in a way that is not

00:48:01.030 --> 00:48:03.790 align:middle line:84%
hurting the earth, and you
don't need infrastructure

00:48:03.790 --> 00:48:06.280 align:middle line:90%
of any kind to do this.

00:48:06.280 --> 00:48:08.740 align:middle line:84%
And what we need
to do, though, is

00:48:08.740 --> 00:48:12.040 align:middle line:84%
we need to be able to do
it to practice and learn,

00:48:12.040 --> 00:48:16.510 align:middle line:84%
and you can't do that unless
you create a law, like we did,

00:48:16.510 --> 00:48:17.950 align:middle line:90%
to practice and learn.

00:48:17.950 --> 00:48:22.180 align:middle line:84%
But that law, it
still has limitations.

00:48:22.180 --> 00:48:24.460 align:middle line:84%
We got the law passed,
but they're still

00:48:24.460 --> 00:48:28.480 align:middle line:84%
squeezing the law, not out of
malice or anything like that,

00:48:28.480 --> 00:48:31.832 align:middle line:90%
but just out of ignorance.

00:48:31.832 --> 00:48:33.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: First of all,
that little house took,

00:48:33.790 --> 00:48:35.100 align:middle line:84%
what, two weeks
to build, roughly?

00:48:35.100 --> 00:48:35.610 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Yeah.

00:48:35.610 --> 00:48:37.401 align:middle line:10%
>>REGINA: The whole
community was watching.

00:48:37.401 --> 00:48:40.180 align:middle line:10%
Pretty much everyone left there
was watching, more or less.

00:48:40.180 --> 00:48:41.710 align:middle line:84%
You had that main
architect with you

00:48:41.710 --> 00:48:43.630 align:middle line:90%
who was really spearheading it.

00:48:43.630 --> 00:48:46.065 align:middle line:84%
And you said, you left behind
a very simple set of plans,

00:48:46.065 --> 00:48:46.510 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:48:46.510 --> 00:48:47.310 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: Yeah.

00:48:47.310 --> 00:48:51.140 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And so really, did
they continue replicating these

00:48:51.140 --> 00:48:51.940 align:middle line:90%
there?

00:48:51.940 --> 00:48:52.740 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:48:52.740 --> 00:48:55.090 align:middle line:10%
>>REYNOLDS: They continued
using the techniques

00:48:55.090 --> 00:48:57.310 align:middle line:10%
for various things.

00:48:57.310 --> 00:48:59.770 align:middle line:10%
That's another thing that
we've learned over the years,

00:48:59.770 --> 00:49:02.590 align:middle line:10%
and now, we're really
employing it in Puerto Rico.

00:49:02.590 --> 00:49:04.600 align:middle line:90%
We employed it on Easter Island.

00:49:04.600 --> 00:49:07.060 align:middle line:90%
We employed it in Sierra Leone.

00:49:07.060 --> 00:49:13.510 align:middle line:84%
And that is, we have to present
these techniques in such a way

00:49:13.510 --> 00:49:15.640 align:middle line:90%
that they can be replicated.

00:49:15.640 --> 00:49:17.980 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it's just
another learning experience.

00:49:17.980 --> 00:49:21.090 align:middle line:84%
It took us a while to figure
out that we have to make

00:49:21.090 --> 00:49:23.880 align:middle line:90%
these things easy to replicate.

00:49:23.880 --> 00:49:28.650 align:middle line:84%
And then that's like a
Petri dish or something.

00:49:28.650 --> 00:49:31.380 align:middle line:84%
A bacteria is not going to
grow, unless the temperature is

00:49:31.380 --> 00:49:36.630 align:middle line:84%
right, and the medium in
the Petri dish is right,

00:49:36.630 --> 00:49:39.040 align:middle line:84%
and there's enough
moisture, and so on.

00:49:39.040 --> 00:49:41.850 align:middle line:84%
We have to create
a situation where

00:49:41.850 --> 00:49:43.980 align:middle line:90%
these things can be replicated.

00:49:43.980 --> 00:49:46.110 align:middle line:84%
No matter how good they
are, if the people there

00:49:46.110 --> 00:49:49.350 align:middle line:84%
can't replicate them, we
haven't really succeeded.

00:49:49.350 --> 00:49:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're trying
to do now in Puerto Rico.

00:49:52.350 --> 00:49:54.690 align:middle line:10%
And it is working
in Puerto Rico.

00:49:54.690 --> 00:49:58.590 align:middle line:10%
We were down there a few
weeks ago, started building.

00:49:58.590 --> 00:50:01.740 align:middle line:10%
I actually got my architect's
license in Puerto Rico, too.

00:50:01.740 --> 00:50:04.050 align:middle line:84%
And we started
building, and they

00:50:04.050 --> 00:50:07.930 align:middle line:84%
have continued, at a slow
pace, with the project.

00:50:07.930 --> 00:50:10.050 align:middle line:84%
And now, we're going
back to show them more,

00:50:10.050 --> 00:50:13.330 align:middle line:84%
and it is working
like a virus there.

00:50:13.330 --> 00:50:14.890 align:middle line:84%
And in many places
around the world,

00:50:14.890 --> 00:50:16.560 align:middle line:90%
it is working like a virus.

00:50:16.560 --> 00:50:21.180 align:middle line:84%
We're just getting to understand
the magic of the virus.

00:50:21.180 --> 00:50:23.400 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and
you say, a sixth grader

00:50:23.400 --> 00:50:25.410 align:middle line:84%
could understand these
plans, for the most part.

00:50:25.410 --> 00:50:26.365 align:middle line:90%
They're that simple.

00:50:26.365 --> 00:50:27.240 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: They are.

00:50:27.240 --> 00:50:29.940 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Even though it has
geothermal implications and all

00:50:29.940 --> 00:50:30.810 align:middle line:90%
that, it's still--

00:50:30.810 --> 00:50:33.740 align:middle line:84%
there's digging in the dirt
and there's circulation,

00:50:33.740 --> 00:50:35.290 align:middle line:84%
and it's still
relatively simple.

00:50:35.290 --> 00:50:36.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REYNOLDS: It is.

00:50:36.090 --> 00:50:40.810 align:middle line:84%
It is simple, and it's just
got to be presented simple.

00:50:40.810 --> 00:50:45.510 align:middle line:84%
In the last seven or so years,
we've started an academy,

00:50:45.510 --> 00:50:47.100 align:middle line:84%
and we have an
earthship academy,

00:50:47.100 --> 00:50:51.000 align:middle line:84%
where we have 300 or
400 students a year

00:50:51.000 --> 00:50:53.130 align:middle line:90%
come through the academy.

00:50:53.130 --> 00:50:55.120 align:middle line:84%
And we do the academy
in New Mexico,

00:50:55.120 --> 00:50:58.050 align:middle line:84%
and we do some sessions
around the world.

00:50:58.050 --> 00:51:01.680 align:middle line:90%
And the students are seeing--

00:51:01.680 --> 00:51:05.420 align:middle line:84%
they're resonating with
the potential of this.

00:51:05.420 --> 00:51:07.950 align:middle line:84%
And a very interesting
thing is, like say

00:51:07.950 --> 00:51:10.560 align:middle line:84%
we have a session that
has 40 students in it,

00:51:10.560 --> 00:51:14.220 align:middle line:84%
at the end of the
session, at least half

00:51:14.220 --> 00:51:16.110 align:middle line:84%
the students don't
want to leave.

00:51:16.110 --> 00:51:16.380 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I'm sure.

00:51:16.380 --> 00:51:17.790 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: You graduate
from Yale or Harvard,

00:51:17.790 --> 00:51:19.890 align:middle line:84%
you want to get to hell
out of there, quick.

00:51:19.890 --> 00:51:22.830 align:middle line:84%
And you graduate from this,
and they don't want to leave.

00:51:22.830 --> 00:51:26.320 align:middle line:84%
They don't want to go back to
the other life that they had.

00:51:26.320 --> 00:51:29.130 align:middle line:84%
So we know that we're
resonating with something

00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:31.260 align:middle line:90%
that's in people already.

00:51:31.260 --> 00:51:33.360 align:middle line:84%
And we know that we've
got a long way to go,

00:51:33.360 --> 00:51:38.190 align:middle line:84%
but it is that little pinpoint
of light in the darkness.

00:51:38.190 --> 00:51:41.850 align:middle line:84%
And the more rocks we pull
away from it, the more--

00:51:41.850 --> 00:51:45.740 align:middle line:84%
the bigger that light
will be as a way out.

00:51:45.740 --> 00:51:48.000 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's
important for me

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:53.130 align:middle line:84%
to realize that I didn't
invent or create that light.

00:51:53.130 --> 00:51:57.450 align:middle line:84%
I found it, and I'm trying to
make the hole through to it

00:51:57.450 --> 00:51:58.650 align:middle line:90%
bigger for everybody.

00:51:58.650 --> 00:52:00.120 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Very
true, and yet, you

00:52:00.120 --> 00:52:01.770 align:middle line:84%
have some earthly
obstacles, such as,

00:52:01.770 --> 00:52:03.060 align:middle line:90%
how do you get access to land?

00:52:03.060 --> 00:52:05.220 align:middle line:84%
How do you get
ownership of land?

00:52:05.220 --> 00:52:08.010 align:middle line:84%
How did you end up on
these deserted islands?

00:52:08.010 --> 00:52:10.270 align:middle line:90%
Did you have to buy the island?

00:52:10.270 --> 00:52:11.990 align:middle line:90%
How does that work?

00:52:11.990 --> 00:52:15.870 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: All of these things,
the more you do, the more you

00:52:15.870 --> 00:52:17.880 align:middle line:90%
cause things to happen.

00:52:17.880 --> 00:52:19.560 align:middle line:84%
For instance, the
Indonesia island,

00:52:19.560 --> 00:52:23.460 align:middle line:84%
they contacted
me, because Bali--

00:52:23.460 --> 00:52:28.510 align:middle line:84%
which is a destination
resort area--

00:52:28.510 --> 00:52:31.980 align:middle line:84%
the reason people came there was
because of the beautiful coral

00:52:31.980 --> 00:52:33.397 align:middle line:90%
and the beauty and everything.

00:52:33.397 --> 00:52:35.730 align:middle line:84%
Well, now, with thousands and
thousands of people there,

00:52:35.730 --> 00:52:38.370 align:middle line:84%
sewage going into the
sea, diesel fluid going

00:52:38.370 --> 00:52:40.620 align:middle line:84%
into the sea for
power and energy,

00:52:40.620 --> 00:52:43.410 align:middle line:84%
they are ruining the
place that people--

00:52:43.410 --> 00:52:45.840 align:middle line:84%
they're ruining what
people came there to see.

00:52:45.840 --> 00:52:49.200 align:middle line:84%
And Indonesia has, I don't
know, thousands of islands,

00:52:49.200 --> 00:52:51.270 align:middle line:84%
and they don't want the
rest of their islands

00:52:51.270 --> 00:52:54.170 align:middle line:90%
to be going in that direction.

00:52:54.170 --> 00:52:56.970 align:middle line:84%
They've got on to what
they call sustainability.

00:52:56.970 --> 00:52:59.100 align:middle line:84%
And it's an overused
word, and a lot of people

00:52:59.100 --> 00:53:00.220 align:middle line:90%
don't know what it means.

00:53:00.220 --> 00:53:03.150 align:middle line:84%
But they want to develop
the rest of the islands

00:53:03.150 --> 00:53:06.060 align:middle line:84%
in a more sustainable way,
so they don't get destroyed.

00:53:06.060 --> 00:53:10.290 align:middle line:84%
They heard, through the
internet, that we do this,

00:53:10.290 --> 00:53:13.980 align:middle line:90%
or we attempt to do this.

00:53:13.980 --> 00:53:15.600 align:middle line:90%
It's a 30 acre island.

00:53:15.600 --> 00:53:19.800 align:middle line:84%
I was offered a third of the
island to do whatever I want

00:53:19.800 --> 00:53:22.980 align:middle line:84%
and then help them do the
same on the other 20 acres.

00:53:22.980 --> 00:53:26.010 align:middle line:84%
So that's how we ended up
with the island in Indonesia.

00:53:26.010 --> 00:53:28.080 align:middle line:84%
And that situation
started something.

00:53:28.080 --> 00:53:30.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm getting offered land
all over the world right now

00:53:30.570 --> 00:53:33.010 align:middle line:90%
on those terms.

00:53:33.010 --> 00:53:35.430 align:middle line:84%
Actually, I don't care
if I own the land.

00:53:35.430 --> 00:53:38.310 align:middle line:84%
The agreement says I get to
use the land for 35 years.

00:53:38.310 --> 00:53:39.630 align:middle line:90%
Well, that's enough for me.

00:53:39.630 --> 00:53:41.526 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: That should do it.

00:53:41.526 --> 00:53:44.690 align:middle line:84%
>>REYNOLDS: So that's
the other thing.

00:53:44.690 --> 00:53:47.370 align:middle line:84%
We don't care who owns
the building or the land

00:53:47.370 --> 00:53:48.240 align:middle line:90%
or anything.

00:53:48.240 --> 00:53:49.830 align:middle line:84%
We want the building
to be there.

00:53:49.830 --> 00:53:51.430 align:middle line:90%
We want people to use it.

00:53:51.430 --> 00:53:53.430 align:middle line:90%
I was just in Puerto Rico.

00:53:53.430 --> 00:53:59.340 align:middle line:84%
And there, we had funders,
big corporations considering

00:53:59.340 --> 00:54:01.080 align:middle line:90%
funding us to go there.

00:54:01.080 --> 00:54:05.400 align:middle line:84%
And when they found out
we didn't know or care

00:54:05.400 --> 00:54:08.340 align:middle line:84%
who owned the land or who was
going to own the building,

00:54:08.340 --> 00:54:10.860 align:middle line:84%
we were just doing it
involving a bunch of people

00:54:10.860 --> 00:54:13.350 align:middle line:84%
and making it
happen, they said, we

00:54:13.350 --> 00:54:17.610 align:middle line:84%
can't function under
these loose situations.

00:54:17.610 --> 00:54:19.170 align:middle line:90%
And so we're funded.

00:54:19.170 --> 00:54:21.170 align:middle line:84%
We're getting funded
by people themselves.

00:54:21.170 --> 00:54:23.510 align:middle line:84%
People all over the
world are coming

00:54:23.510 --> 00:54:26.870 align:middle line:84%
and paying to come and help
us, and that funds the project.

00:54:26.870 --> 00:54:36.230 align:middle line:84%
